						               													<description>Red vs White vs Blue is a block wargame about the four year long struggle in Russia after the 1917 October Revolution. One player controls the Red (Bolshevik) forces, the other the Whites (anti-Bolshevik, a collection of different factions). One unique aspect of the game that there are also Blue blocks: these represent the Separatist forces (e.g. the Baltic Republics) that want to remain neutral and independent.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Unit types include Infantry, Cavalry, Tanks, Armored Trains, specialized White units (Cossacks, Volunteers, Czechoslovak Legion, Baltic Germans, Finns etc.) and several leaders for all three sides.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Both players have their own deck of 16 action cards, from which they draw 7 and use 5 per turn. The cards govern the players' actions (e.g. Comintern, leader activations, recruitment, terror). The game is 10 turns long.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has a fully playable VASSAL module! You can download it from here: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1VsyFa2c6fmKo_DSyNi2-BqRcZgCsCfze/view?usp=sharing&amp;#10;&amp;#10;COMPONENTS&amp;#10;1 map of Russia&amp;#10;70 blocks&amp;#10;32 action cards&amp;#10;4 markers&amp;#10;1 rulebook&amp;#10;several dice&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is PnP, which means that the components are freely downloadable! Please note however, that the blocks and the dice are not included, you have to supply these yourself.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
